  "response": "Surviving a 100-foot drop into water depends on several factors:\n\n1. Water conditions:\n- Surface of water (calm vs. rough)\n- Depth of water\n- Presence of underwater obstacles\n\n2. Body positioning:\n- Feet-first entry\n- Proper vertical alignment\n- Arms close to body\n\n3. Physical factors:\n- Personal physical condition\n- Ability to enter water correctly\n\nGenerally, a 100-foot drop is extremely dangerous and likely fatal. Professional cliff divers typically jump from much lower heights. Even with perfect technique, the impact force can cause severe injury or death. Water does not necessarily cushion a fall from such a height effectively.\n\nSurvival probability is very low, and attempting such a drop would be extremely risky and not recommended under any circumstances.",
